# Component Standards

All UI components MUST use shadcn/ui components. Do not create custom implementations when a shadcn component exists.

## Rules

- **Always use shadcn components** from `@/components/ui` instead of custom implementations
- **Check existing components first** - see `src/components/ui/` for available components
- **Add new shadcn components** using the shadcn CLI when needed, don't build from scratch
- **Follow shadcn patterns** - use `cva` (class-variance-authority) for variants, `cn` utility for className merging

## Examples

### ✅ Good - Using shadcn Button

```typescript
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

export const MyComponent = () => {
  return <Button variant="default">Click me</Button>;
};
```

### ❌ Bad - Custom button implementation

```typescript
// Don't create custom buttons when shadcn Button exists
export const MyComponent = () => {
  return <button className="bg-blue-500 text-white px-4 py-2">Click me</button>;
};
```

